overview_summary: Of the two neighboring landowners, neither has a clear public stance on the development (both are noted as "unknown" stance). One neighbor is a long-established dairy farming operation with high community influence due to its economic and social presence, whereas the other is an individual landowner with a low-profile and limited influence in local affairs.

neighbors.name: Blue Star Dairy Farms
neighbors.claims: Blue Star Dairy Farms is a long-established dairy operation in DeForest, Wisconsin, founded in 1946 and incorporated in the state [Manta](https://www.manta.com/c/mm7c6z9/blue-star-dairy-farms). It has been active in the farming community, even hosting Dane County’s annual dairy breakfast events in past years [Dane County Dairy](https://www.danecountydairy.org/past-hosts).

approach_recommendations.engage: Have a respected agricultural liaison reach out to discuss how the project can coexist with farming operations, emphasizing protections for their farmland and local road infrastructure.

neighbors.name: Cynthia M. LaValley
neighbors.claims: County records list Cynthia M. LaValley’s property under a life estate, meaning she has transferred title to someone else but retains the right to live on and benefit from the land during her lifetime [Wisconsin DHS](https://www.emhandbooks.wisconsin.gov/meh-ebd/history/15-03/15-03_17.10.htm). She holds no public office or known activist role in the community, and her name does not appear in local civic records or news regarding development issues [Town of Vienna](https://www.viennawi.gov/).

approach_recommendations.engage: Engage via a personal, respectful approach (possibly involving her family or long-time community contacts) and emphasize how the proposal respects her land’s legacy and keeps the family’s farmland values intact.
